{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Job|41","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","chapter":41,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":1,"text":"Can you pull in Leviathan with a hook or tie his tongue down with a rope?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":2,"text":"Can you put a cord through his nose or pierce his jaw with a hook?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":3,"text":"Will he beg you for mercy or speak softly to you?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":4,"text":"Will he make a covenant with you so that you can take him as a slave forever?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":5,"text":"Can you play with him like a bird or put him on a leash for your girls?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":6,"text":"Will traders bargain for him or divide him among the merchants?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":7,"text":"Can you fill his hide with harpoons or his head with fishing spears?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":8,"text":"Lay a hand on him. You will remember the battle and never repeat it!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":9,"text":"Any hope of capturing him proves false. Does a person not collapse at the very sight of him?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":10,"text":"No one is ferocious enough to rouse Leviathan; who then can stand against me?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":11,"text":"Who confronted me, that I should repay him? Everything under heaven belongs to me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":12,"text":"I cannot be silent about his limbs, his power, and his graceful proportions.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":13,"text":"Who can strip off his outer covering? Who can penetrate his double layer of armor?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":14,"text":"Who can open his jaws, surrounded by those terrifying teeth?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":15,"text":"His pride is in his rows of scales, closely sealed together.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":16,"text":"One scale is so close to another that no air can pass between them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":17,"text":"They are joined to one another, so closely connected they cannot be separated.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":18,"text":"His snorting flashes with light, while his eyes are like the rays of dawn.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":19,"text":"Flaming torches shoot from his mouth; fiery sparks fly out!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":20,"text":"Smoke billows from his nostrils as from a boiling pot or burning reeds.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":21,"text":"His breath sets coals ablaze, and flames pour out of his mouth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":22,"text":"Strength resides in his neck, and dismay dances before him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":23,"text":"The folds of his flesh are joined together, solid as metal and immovable.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":24,"text":"His heart is as hard as a rock, as hard as a lower millstone!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":25,"text":"When Leviathan rises, the mighty are terrified; they withdraw because of his thrashing.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":26,"text":"The sword that reaches him will have no effect, nor will a spear, dart, or arrow.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":27,"text":"He regards iron as straw, and bronze as rotten wood.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":28,"text":"No arrow can make him flee; slingstones become like stubble to him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":29,"text":"A club is regarded as stubble, and he laughs at the sound of a javelin.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":30,"text":"His undersides are jagged potsherds, spreading the mud like a threshing sledge.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":31,"text":"He makes the depths seethe like a cauldron; he makes the sea like an ointment jar.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:41:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":41,"verse":32,"text":"He lea